Ingredients:

3 eggs, separated
3 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon baking soda
1 cup whole milk
1/2 cup butter, softened
1/2 cup sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla
2 cups blueberries
1 (12-ounce) container ricotta
2 tablespoons whole milk
Zest of 1 lemon
2 tablespoons lemon juice
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and spray the bottoms and sides of six 5-inch pie pans with nonstick spray.

2. In a medium bowl, whip the egg whites.

3. In another medium bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda. Stir in the milk.

4. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and yolks.

5. Mix in flour mixture, then fold in the whites, followed by the vanilla.

6. Divide batter between the prepared tins.

7. Divide blueberries between the tins to cover the tops of the custards.

8. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

9. Add ricotta and milk to a bowl. Whip with a whisk until smooth.

10. Add lemon zest and juice and vanilla.

11. Spoon onto pies and serve warm.

node.title: Your weekend baking plans: Blueberry custard w/ whipped lemon ricotta.

On this week's "Disney's Magic Bake-Off," Kenady & Cayley used their decorating skills to whip up a cake full of enchantment. 

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW!

Coconut Pineapple Lime Cake

Ingredients:

1 c salted butter
2 c Sugar
6 eggs
1 T coconut emulsion
1 T Lime extract
3 t Baking Powder
2 t salt
2 t tart and sour flavoring
4 c AP flour
2  c whole milk
½ c fresh pineapple
½ c coconut shreds
2 c salted butter
4 c Powdered Sugar
2-3 T heavy cream
1 T coconut emulsion
1 T lime extract
1 t pineapple juice
½ juice of a lime
2 t salt
1 T ground ginger

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350.

2. In a mixer cream butter and sugar.

3. Add eggs one at a time until well incorporated.

4. Add coconut emulsion and lime extract.

5. In a medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.

6. Alternate between milk and dry ingredients into creamed butter and sugar.

7. Fold in pineapple and coconut shreds.

8. Pour into 2- 6” pans and 2-8” pans and bake for 25- 30 mins.

9. Once cakes are completely cooled, frost and enjoy.

10. In a clean mixer bowl cream butter on high.

11. Add coconut emulsion, lime extract, pineapple juice, lime juice, salt, and ground ginger. Mix until well combined.

12. Add powdered sugar 1 cup at a time. If the frosting is too thick add heavy cream 1T at a time.

node.title: Flowers, pearls & a "glass" dome make this cake fit for a modern princess!

Ingredients:

For the espresso brownies:
4 eggs
1 1/2 cups sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 cup butter, melted
2 tablespoons espresso powder
1/2 cup cocoa powder
1 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
3 (8-ounce) packages cream cheese, softened
1 1/2 cups sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla bean paste
3 large eggs, room temperature, divided
1/2 cup pumpkin puree
1/2 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice
In the prepared baking dish, pour the cream cheese mixture on top of the brownie batter and smooth to cover. Dollop 1-tablespoon portions of the pumpkin mixture in rows across the cream cheese. Use a knife or toothpick to create a swirl pattern, being careful not to go too deep to pull up any espresso brownie batter and without overworking the cream cheese topping.
Tent with foil, and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until cheese is set. Cool to room temperature, and chill for at least 30 minutes before slicing.

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees, and prepare a 9 by 13-inch baking dish with parchment paper and nonstick spray.

2. In a large mixing bowl, whisk eggs, sugar and vanilla. Slowly pour in the melted butter and whisk to combine. Fold in the espresso, cocoa powder, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir to combine but don’t over mix. Pour into the prepared baking dish and set aside.

3. In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla and 2 eggs, and beat until incorporated. Set aside.

4. In a small mixing bowl, stir together pumpkin puree, pumpkin pie spice and the remaining egg.

The secret ingredient to these crispy chicken parmesan pillows? The perfect pot! We love our vintage-retro Dansk Casserole dish, and you will too: 
https://prf.hn/l/KMEV2MB

#promotion

Ingredients:

1 package crescent rolls
1 chicken breast, thinly sliced
1 tablespoon dried parsley
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried oregano
Salt
Pepper
Olive oil
8 ounces mozzarella cheese
Marinara sauce, for dipping
For the dredge:
2 cups Italian-style breadcrumbs
1 cup Parmesan cheese
3 eggs, beaten
3 cups all-purpose flour
Oil, for frying

Steps:

1. In a bowl, combine the chicken breast, dried parsley, dried thyme, dried oregano, salt, pepper and olive oil and toss to combine. Place chicken on a medium-high pan and cook on both sides until the internal temperature reaches 165 degrees. Once cooked, take chicken off the pan and allow to cool.

2. Using two pieces of the crescent dough, form a rectangle. Top one side of the dough with cheese and a piece of chicken. Add another layer of cheese over the chicken, and fold over the crescent dough so that it forms a pillow. Crimp the edges of the dough to properly seal closed.

3. In a small bowl, combine the breadcrumbs and the Parmesan cheese. Set up a dredging station with the beaten eggs, flour and breadcrumb mixture. Dredge each pillow by coating with flour first, then egg, and then the breadcrumb mixture. Shake off any excess breadcrumbs.

4. In a large heavy-bottomed stock pot or deep-fryer, heat vegetable oil to 350 degrees. Carefully add 1 or 2 pillows at a time and cook until golden brown. Remove and drain on a cooling rack.

5. Place all the pillows on a lined baking sheet, and put in a 350 degree oven for 10 minutes. Allow to cool slightly before serving. Serve alongside marinara sauce for dipping.

Taking inspiration from Disneyland Park's Mad Tea Party attraction, Ella & Ivy designed a topsy-turvy dessert fit for Alice and the Mad Hatter on this week's "Disney's Magic Bake-Off."
 
Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW! 

Ingredients:

½ c sour cream
1 c whole milk
½ T apple cider vinegar
3 large eggs
4 T instant coffee dissolved into 1 ½  c water
¾ c vegetable oil
1 T vanilla extract
3  c ap flour
2 ⅔ c granulated sugar
½ c cocoa powder
½ T baking powder
1 T baking soda
1 t salt
1 t chai spice
½ t cinnamon
2 c ap flour
1 ½ sticks unsalted butter
½ c granulated sugar
1 c brown sugar
1 t salt
1 T vanilla
½ c milk
½ c cocoa powder
1 ½ c chocolate chips

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350

2. Mix together all wet ingredients (sour cream, milk, vinegar, eggs, coffee, oil, and vanilla) in a large bowl.

3. In a separate large bowl, sift the flour, sugar, salt, cocoa powder, baking powder, chai spice, cinnamon, and baking soda, and mix together to combine.

4. Add the wet mixture into the dry mixture and whisk until a fully combined batter is formed.

5. Spray 2-6” pans and 2-8” pan with canola spray and line it with a parchment round.

6. Distribute the batter evenly between the pans.

7. Bake the cake layers in the preheated oven until a knife inserted comes out clean about 30-40 minutes.

8. Let cake layers cool in the pan for 10-15 minutes and then release them onto a cooling rack.

9. Level the tops with a serrated knife.

10. Once cakes have cooled add cookie dough disks between cake layers and frost.

11. In a clean mixer bowl cream butter and sugar until well combined.

12. Add salt, vanilla and cocoa powder. Once well incorporated, alternate between flour and milk. Fold in chocolate chips.

13. Wrap a 6” and 4” pan in plastic wrap. Push cookie dough in them to form perfect disks for filling and place in the fridge.

Nutella Stuffed Banana Bread

Ingredients:

2 large eggs, divided
1/3 cup powdered sugar
2/3 cup Nutella
5 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted
3 tablespoons vegetable oil
3 large, super ripe bananas, mashed well
1/2 cup light brown sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 1/2 cups flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
1/4 teaspoon salt
4 bananas, thinly sliced

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a loaf pan.

2. In a bowl, whisk 1 egg and the powdered sugar until foamy. Fold in Nutella until evenly incorporated.

3. In a large bowl, combine the butter, vegetable oil and mashed bananas. Whisk in the second egg, light brown sugar and vanilla extract until smooth and thick.

4. In another bowl, whisk flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon and salt. Fold the dry ingredients into the banana/butter mixture until just evenly combined, but not over-worked.

5. Pour two-thirds of the batter into the prepared loaf pan.

6. Line up three-fourths of the thinly sliced bananas along the batter, then top with a layer of Nutella mixture.

7. Cover with a final layer of the remaining batter.

8. Using a toothpick or skewer, gently swirl the top layer and the Nutella together without disturbing the banana slices.

9. Top with slices of bananas, facing up.

10. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until a wooden skewer comes out clean from the banana layer, but bread is still runny and gooey in the center of the molten chocolate. Let cool in the pan for 15 minutes before removing.

node.title: Reward your sweet tooth with Nutella-stuffed banana bread.

Ingredients:

3 tablespoons warm water
1 packet active dry yeast
1 teaspoon sugar
1/4 cup butter
1/3 cup whole milk
3 cups all-purpose flour
1/4 cup sugar
1 teaspoon salt
2 large eggs, beaten
1 teaspoon vanilla

Steps:

1. In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the dough hook attachment, combine water, yeast and sugar. Activate the yeast for 5 minutes, or until foamy.

2. In a small saucepan, heat butter and milk until butter melts and reaches 120 degrees. Set aside.

3. In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Add to yeast mixture. Add eggs, vanilla and milk mixture to the stand mixer bowl and combine on low for 2 to 3 minutes until dough starts to come together. Once mixed, knead for 3 minutes until dough is shiny and elastic. Transfer to a large greased bowl and cover for an hour until dough doubles in size.

4. Spray a 9x5 loaf pan with nonstick spray and line with parchment paper.

5. Roll risen dough out on a floured surface to approximately 20 by 12 inches. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture. Press nut mixture across the dough evenly.  Cut dough into 6 strips lengthwise and stack each strip on top of each other. Cut into 4 even squares and stack standing up in loaf pan. Cover with plastic wrap and let dough rise for approximately one hour until it fills out the pan.

6. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.

7. Bake bread for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden. Once cooled, remove from pan and drizzle with honey rosewater syrup. Bread will keep up to 4 days covered.

node.title: Bring this baklava pull-apart bread to your next shindig.

Aaron & Michael brought the magic of Auradon to life with this stunning "Descendants"-themed cake on this week's episode of "Disney's Magic Bake-Off."

Catch future cake creations every Friday at 8/7c, and watch past clips only on @disneychannel and DisneyNOW!

Classic Lemon Cake with Orange Cranberry Filling

Ingredients:

2/3 c lemon juice
1 ⅓  c whole milk
2 ½ c granulated sugar
Zest from 3 lemons
1 c Unsalted Butter
6 eggs
2 t vanilla extract
4 T lemon extract
4  c AP Flour
3 t Baking Powder
1 t Baking Soda
2  t Salt
1 Stick Salted Butter
3 oz Cream Cheese
1 lb Powdered Sugar
Zest of 1 whole orange
1 T orange extract
1 lemon
Fresh or dried cranberries

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 350.

2. Mix Lemon juice and milk and set aside .

3. Pulse sugar & Zest in food processor. Set aside.

4. In a mixer cream butter then add sugar and zest mixture.

5. Add eggs one at a time until well incorporated.

6. In a medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

7. Alternate between milk mixture and dry ingredients into creamed butter and sugar.

8. Fold in vanilla and lemon extract.

9. Pour into 2- 6” pans and 2-8” pans and bake for 25- 30 mins. Let cool, then frost and enjoy!

10. In a saucepan add orange extract, a few drops of lemon, and cranberries. Let simmer.

11. Once mixture has simmered, strain and add orange zest. Set aside and let cool.

12. In a mixing bowl add a stick of butter and cream cheese, cream together till smooth.

13. Add Powdered sugar one cup at a time.

14. Once powdered sugar is incorporated add orange zest mixture.

15. Mix until smooth.

node.title: The most important royal wedding of the summer deserves a fitting cake!

Our mac 'n' cheese-stuffed parmesan pesto burger is sincerely the right amount of extra. 

Ingredients:

1 Lb ground steak
2 tbsp mild paprika
1 tsp chili flakes
3 tbsp worcestershire sauce
1 tsp dried onion
1 cup grated young parmesan cheese
1/2 cup grated mozzarella
1 Cup Cooked Macaroni al Dente
1 Cup fresh basil
1 Grated Parmesan Cheese
1/2 Mozzarella Cheese
1 tbsp Grated garlic
1 tsp sea salt
1 tbsp grated black pepper
Extra Virgin Olive Oil
1/4 cup heavy cream
2 Fried eggs
Parmesan shaves
Chili flakes
2 burger brioche buns seared in the griddle
4 tbsp pesto
1 tbsp Butter
2 Parmesan stuffed burgers
3 cups french fries

Steps:

1. Mix together in a large bowl the ground steak, paprika, chili flakes, worcestershire sauce, and dry onion

2. Press one big scoop of the mix to form a half an inch disc

3. in the center of this dicsc put 1/2 cup grated parmesan cheese amd 1/4 cup grated mozzarella, and cover with an other half an inch grated steak mix

4. Repeat the process and chill in the freezer for 15 minutes

5. In a blender mix fresh basil, 1/2 cup grated parmesan cheese, grated garlic, salt and pepper

6. Once everything is finely chopped, add Extra Virgin Olive Oil until the mix gets a waterish but scoopable thickness

7. Add the heavy cream and mix for only 30 seconds or until well combined

8. Mix the pesto, 1/2 cup grated mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup remaining Parmesan cheese in a bowl

9. Add hot macaroni al dente right before putting together the burgers

10. Reserve 4 tbsp of pesto for the burger buns

11. Sear the burgers in a griddle or plancha for 5 minutes on each side and let to rest

12. Sear brioche buns cut side down in the grease of the burger and add a tbsp of butter

13. Once golden, place a tbsp of pesto on each cut side of the bun

14. In order, top with the stuffed burgers, mac n' cheese, one fried egg each, shaved parmesan and chili flakes to taste

15. *a metal cake ring the size of your burgers can be useful for the forming of the final burger

16. Serve with french fries and more sauce for dipping, if desired

Grilled corn on the cob just got an upgrade; for a side dish that'll truly steal the show this summer, fire up these elote riblets and wash them down with a refreshing @estrellajalisco Tropical Chamoy Michelada. #ad

Chef's choice: No barbecue is complete without a side dish of ____. 

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon brown sugar
2 teaspoons ancho chilli powder (or paprika)
2 teaspoons arbol chilli powder (or cayenne)
2 teaspoons guajillo chilli powder (or mild chilli powder)
2 teaspoons dried oregano
1 teaspoon salt
8 tablespoons vegetable or olive oil
4 corn on the cob
4 limes
Cilantro, a handful
¼ cup mayonnaise
½ cup cotija cheese (or feta)

Steps:

1. Make the spice rub: Put the brown sugar, chilli powders, oregano and salt into a large mixing bowl. Mix, then reserve 1 tablespoon of the spice mix. Add the oil and stir well.

2. Prepare the riblets: Trim the ends off each cob of corn so they are flat at both ends. Stand one up vertically, then use a sharp knife to carefully cut it down the middle. Repeat to cut each half into three riblets, then do the same to the rest of the corn.

3. Use your hands to toss the riblets in the spice rub, making sure they’re well covered. Heat a flame grill and use tongs to cook the riblets in batches, for around 1-2 minutes each, turning often.

4. To serve: Pile the flame-grilled riblets onto a large serving platter and load up with drizzled mayo, crumbled cheese, cilantro and freshly squeezed lime.

Ingredients:

3 eggs, separated
3 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon baking soda
1 cup whole milk
1/2 cup butter, softened
1/2 cup sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla
2 cups blueberries
1 (12-ounce) container ricotta
2 tablespoons whole milk
Zest of 1 lemon
2 tablespoons lemon juice
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and spray the bottoms and sides of six 5-inch pie pans with nonstick spray.

2. In a medium bowl, whip the egg whites.

3. In another medium bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda. Stir in the milk.

4. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and yolks.

5. Mix in flour mixture, then fold in the whites, followed by the vanilla.

6. Divide batter between the prepared tins.

7. Divide blueberries between the tins to cover the tops of the custards.

8. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

9. Add ricotta and milk to a bowl. Whip with a whisk until smooth.

10. Add lemon zest and juice and vanilla.

11. Spoon onto pies and serve warm.

Look, maybe we got off on the wrong foot with the 🍕 cones. So here's a nice baked bean pizza to smooth things over.

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Ingredients:

200ml milk
300g strong white bread flour
1 tsp fast-action dried yeast
1/2 tsp caster sugar, plus a pinch
1 tsp salt
2 tbsp olive oil
150g mozzarella, from a block, cut into long strips
1 tsp hot smoked paprika
1 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp garlic granules
1/2 tsp ground coriander
1/2 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp cayenne pepper
1/2 tsp english mustard powder
1 tsp soft brown sugar
2 x 200g tins baked beans
1 tsp worcestershire sauce
1 tsp tabasco
1 long red chilli, finely sliced

Steps:

1. Warm the milk in a saucepan until steaming but not boiling. In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a dough hook, combine the flour, yeast, sugar and salt and stir to combine. Add 1 tbsp of olive oil to the milk and leave to cool until just warm. With the motor running, pour the liquid into the bowl and continue mixing in for 5-7 mins, until you have a smooth and elastic dough. Transfer the dough to a clean, oiled bowl and cover with cling film. Leave somewhere warm to rise for 1 hr or until doubled in size.

2. Punch the dough down to knock out the air then shape into a disc - you can do this with a rolling pin or with your hands. Roll out the dough to a circle, about 35cm wide then transfer to a circular baking tray. Use the mozzarella to create a ring around the outside edge of the pizza base, leaving 1/2cm gap between the edge, then fold over the outside edge to enclose the mozzarella and create a stuffed crust. 

3. Lightly cover with oiled cling film and set aside for 20-30 mins, until the dough has puffed up a little. Meanwhile heat oven to 240 C / 220 C fan.

4. To make the spiced beans, add all the dry spices to a saucepan set over a medium heat and heat until they start to smell fragrant. Add 1 tsp olive oil, the sugar, the beans, worcestershire sauce and tabasco and stir to combine. Set aside to cool.

5. When cool spread the spiced beans over the pizza base then sprinkle over the cheese and finally top with the sliced red chilli.

6. Bake in the oven for 15 - 20 mins or until golden and risen.
